Preamble (Gratitude + Intent)

This project is indebted to the SQLite project—technically, culturally, and
philosophically. SQLite demonstrated that small, careful software can power
a large fraction of civilization, and it did so while keeping reuse friction
as close to zero as the law allows.

Intent: Public Domain, SQLite-Style

Our intent is that all original code and improvements in this repository be
dedicated to the public domain in the same spirit as SQLite.

In that spirit, and in honor of SQLite, we include the SQLite Blessing:

  The author disclaims copyright to this source code. In place of a legal
  notice, here is a blessing:

  May you do good and not evil.
  May you find forgiveness for yourself and forgive others.
  May you share freely, never taking more than you give.

Legal Reality: Jurisdictions and Policies Vary

Some jurisdictions do not fully recognize public domain dedications, and some
users require an OSI-approved license for compliance, redistribution, or internal
policy. Therefore, in addition to the public-domain intent above, we offer this
project under a tri-license so you can choose what fits your situation.

